Organization = {{Int Inst Informat \& Syst; Int Federat Syst Res}},
Abstract = {{It has been decades that the information systems are widely applied in
   mineral industry to improve the business performance. However, while
   these systems have been improved incrementally over time, there is more
   and more pressure for the individual companies to gain overall control
   of these enterprise disparate systems. The new systems represent giant
   leaps in technology that can give the company great benefit, but it also
   means the great gap between the new and old system. There are two groups
   of problems: Integration and Reengineering. To address the problems, the
   pre-requisite is to understand the total system framework (function
   model, data model, system architecture model) and the information
   resource standards (data standard, information classification standard,
   database standard, etc), which in all can be defined as ``Information
   Resource Planning{''} (IRP). IRP will be the vital infrastructure to
   support the overall enterprise governance, and the core of IRP solution
   for disparate systems is data standardization. A methodology for
   developing the conceptual framework of IRP is introduced here. The final
   framework will be an extensible mineral information model with the
   associated Metadata stored in the repository, which accommodates the
   kinds of basic data entities that software tool can manipulate thus to
   support an enterprise wide information source planning and management.
   The model is fundamentally extensible in the sense that users are
   allowed to define new data entities and their types.}},
