   scheduling in supply chains. It first gives an overview of the various
   planning and scheduling models that have been studied in the literature,
   including lot sizing models and machine scheduling models. It
   subsequently categorizes the various industrial sectors in which
   planning and scheduling in the supply chains are important; these
   industries include continuous manufacturing as well as discrete
