Pages = {{234-251}},
Abstract = {{Given the significant impact of implementing enterprise resources
   planning (ERP), managerial adaptation of ERP offers a useful method of
   further maximizing the benefits of this system. This study employs a
   technology adaptation perspective and case research methodology to
   examine three dimensions of alignment between organization and ERP
   system. Four medium size electronic component manufacturers are
   selected, which are typical of domestic companies that could afford and
   implement ERP. From the findings of the case study, this research
   attempts to build a theoretical model of prescribing management
   strategies for implementing ERP. The findings indicated that the
   requirement for successful alignment between the system and organization
   falls into two categories. The alignment issues in the two categories
   help explain the working of process integration in the organization and
   also how to reduce the alignment gap. To summarize, this study proposes
   an adaptation framework containing a set of propositions and hypotheses
   to delineate the relevant research issues.}},
