   significantly complementing the use of business-to-business c-commerce
   technologies. We consider the sources of this complement by drawing on
   transaction cost economics, and the theory of swift even flow. Analysis
   of 115 firms shows that perceived transactional efficiencies are greater
   for B2B e-commerce technologies in the presence of ERP, and are in fact
   magnified when ERP implementation specifically precedes B2B e-commerce
   initiatives. These findings imply a distinct system adoption strategy
   for firms pursuing e-commerce opportunities. (C) 2004 Elsevier Ltd. All
